      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money isn't just sitting in some random bank account, which is where the real caution comes in—you want a trustworthy entity! Typically, the escrow account is managed by a specialized escrow company or a title company. These professionals are legally bound to hold the funds in a segregated account, meaning that money is kept separate from their own operating funds. This separation is key; it’s not just a regular checking account, which is what keeps the transaction secure.",
