      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the title company is the gatekeeper, ensuring the title is clean—no hidden claims or debts attached to the property. To ensure your deposit is safe, you should absolutely verify that the escrow agent is licensed and reputable. Don't just trust the realtor; ask for the specific escrow company's credentials. It's wise to keep a close eye on the escrow instructions and milestones, just like you'd watch a very cautious, highly organized group of professional gremlins guarding a pile of shiny, highly valuable, but very temporary loot.",
